	<title>Steven Pinker on Will Smith and Hitler</title>

	<category term="Morality" />
	<category term="Psychology" />

	<content type="xhtml">
		<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
			<div class="quote">
				<blockquote cite="http://www.nytimes.com/2008/01/13/magazine/13Psychology-t.html">
					<p>
						The actor Will Smith had many historians on his side when <a href="http://changelog.ca/quote/2009/08/20/will_smith_on_adolf_hitler">he recently speculated</a> to the press that Hitler thought he was acting morally.
					</p>
				</blockquote>
				<p class="quote-by">
					-- <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.stevenpinker.com/">Steven Arthur Pinker</a>
				</p>
				<p class="quote-from">
					from "<a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.nytimes.com/2008/01/13/magazine/13Psychology-t.html">The Moral Instinct</a>"
				</p>
